    <description>I need to install windows xp as a dual boot for a few reasons. Anyways my problem is that right now the only program that i know of for ubuntu is gparted. However gparted will not let me format a partition in ntfs and my wonderful windows xp cd won&#39;t let me format anything to ntf. So any ideas on how to format a partition into ntfs?</description>
    
